1
00:00:01,043 --> 00:00:04,796
(roaring)

2
00:00:04,796 --> 00:00:06,381
Now that the
devastating monster,

3
00:00:06,381 --> 00:00:08,217
Yamigedo has
been revived,

4
00:00:08,217 --> 00:00:10,052
the only way to
seal him away again

5
00:00:10,052 --> 00:00:12,846
is with the power
of the Eight Omni Lords.

6
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:16,808
It's up to us to find them and
there's only one way we can!

7
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:19,102
‐We gotta Buddyfight!
‐We gotta Buddyfight!

8
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:21,230
♪

9
00:00:21,230 --> 00:00:23,315
Fire Lord Bursting Fist!

10
00:00:23,315 --> 00:00:29,613
♪

11
00:00:29,613 --> 00:00:31,406
Uh‐oh.

12
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:33,784
(screams)

13
00:00:33,784 --> 00:00:36,036
Penetrate!

14
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:38,163
(screaming)

15
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:40,165
Say goodnight, 100 Demon!

16
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:42,501
‐Double attack!
‐No chance!

17
00:00:42,501 --> 00:00:44,836
I cast Green
Dragon Shield.

18
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:48,590
Buzz Saw blocks the attack
and regains one life point.

19
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,800
(snickering)

20
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,343
How do you like me now?

21
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:52,552
No way!

22
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:56,473
♪

23
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:57,933
It can't be!

24
00:00:57,933 --> 00:00:59,393
It's not possible.

25
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:01,103
It can and it is.

26
00:01:01,103 --> 00:01:03,855
Triple attack!

27
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:05,357
Who is this guy?

28
00:01:05,357 --> 00:01:07,442
Now for the
final blow, ki!

29
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,569
He did it!

30
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:10,862
♪

31
00:01:10,862 --> 00:02:38,200
♪

32
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:47,125
♪

33
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:49,378
You're kidding right?

34
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:51,713
You got to be,
you wouldn't do this.

35
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:54,091
It's some
kind of prank.

36
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:55,133
Are you serious?

37
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,636
You got to stop beating
yourself up over this.

38
00:02:57,636 --> 00:03:00,681
Think about
what you're saying.

39
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:03,392
No, I've made up my mind.

40
00:03:03,392 --> 00:03:05,185
I'm done.

41
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:08,063
I'm quitting
Buddyfight for good.

42
00:03:14,695 --> 00:03:17,030
But what gives, yo?

43
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,574
At least give us
an explanation.

44
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:22,119
I'm just not
good enough.

45
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,578
Huh?

46
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:26,123
I can't use Dragon
decks anymore.

47
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:27,249
So what?

48
00:03:27,249 --> 00:03:29,876
You could still
use Hero World decks.

49
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:32,838
I lost to Shigamine.

50
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:36,174
It's time for Final Phase.

51
00:03:36,174 --> 00:03:38,844
I'm scared.

52
00:03:38,844 --> 00:03:40,262
I cast!

53
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:41,513
(moaning)

54
00:03:41,513 --> 00:03:43,890
I keep telling you,
you didn't lose that fight.

55
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:47,644
♪

56
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,271
I'm doing what you said.

57
00:03:49,271 --> 00:03:50,689
Don't you remember?

58
00:03:50,689 --> 00:03:53,066
Huh?

59
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:54,860
You have to
listen to me.

60
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,736
There are no heroes
that are going to come

61
00:03:56,736 --> 00:03:59,322
to your aid when
you're in trouble.

62
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:01,366
It's time you realize
that you have to deal

63
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:04,494
with your problems
by yourself.

64
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:07,914
You're right, which is why
I'm gonna quit Buddyfighting.

65
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:10,876
I need to fix my
problems on my own.

66
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:11,960
You missed my point.

67
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,962
Quitting doesn't
fix anything at all.

68
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:15,088
Listen to him!

69
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:17,340
Besides, aren't you
forgetting something, kid?

70
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:20,218
What'll happen
to me if you quit?

71
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:22,971
About that.

72
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:25,515
I think you should
join Tasuku's deck.

73
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:26,892
Huh?

74
00:04:26,892 --> 00:04:30,353
I bet with him you'll be able
to become a true Omni Lord.

75
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:34,357
Is that what
this is all about?

76
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:36,735
You're doing it for me?

77
00:04:36,735 --> 00:04:38,028
Good luck, pal.

78
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:40,113
♪

79
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:41,531
Take good care of him.

80
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:45,368
He can be a little stubborn,
but he's as good as they come.

81
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:48,079
♪

82
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:50,624
(sighs)

83
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:55,170
I'd like to thank you for giving
me the opportunity, Count.

84
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:59,382
But in my condition, I'm
no good to the Buddy Police.

85
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:01,468
Sorry, I couldn't
have done more.

86
00:05:01,468 --> 00:05:03,386
Just please find Noboru.

87
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,013
Yes, of course.

88
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:09,226
♪

89
00:05:09,226 --> 00:05:10,936
You can't!

90
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:14,856
Sorry, pal, and
thanks for everything.

91
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:17,734
Don't cause Tasuku
any trouble now.

92
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:20,028
No wait, Gao!

93
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,530
Please don't leave!

94
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:26,159
♪

95
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:37,838
It just seems weird
without Drum being with us.

96
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:44,094
Yes, it's definitely
much quieter than usual.

97
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:48,223
♪

98
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:50,809
Oh, yeah!

99
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:52,811
It's amazing.

100
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,980
Oh, good, then I'll
have a fresh batch ready

101
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,857
by the time you get
home from school today.

102
00:05:56,857 --> 00:05:58,358
Sweet!

103
00:05:58,358 --> 00:05:59,734
So where is he then, huh?

104
00:05:59,734 --> 00:06:01,570
Is he gonna be
back home tomorrow?

105
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:03,572
♪

106
00:06:03,572 --> 00:06:04,489
Huh?

107
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:07,284
Hana.

108
00:06:07,284 --> 00:06:09,661
You haven't finished
your vegetables.

109
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:12,163
If you must know,
I was saving them for Drum.

110
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:15,250
He usually gets hungry
an hour after we eat.

111
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,793
Thanks for dinner, Dad.

112
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:21,131
♪

113
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:23,592
(door opens, closes)

114
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:24,926
Hmm.

115
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:43,153
♪

116
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:48,199
So, there's still
no word from Gao.

117
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:51,244
‐I'm afraid not.
‐It's been over a week now.

118
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,872
Given that we don't
know Jack's whereabouts,

119
00:06:53,872 --> 00:06:57,459
it may be time to consider
making Drum your official buddy.

120
00:07:04,049 --> 00:07:06,635
Don't you miss him at all?

121
00:07:06,635 --> 00:07:08,720
Huh?

122
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:12,891
Is he ever gonna come
and live with us again?

123
00:07:12,891 --> 00:07:16,770
Gao Mikado,
is that you?

124
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,105
(chuckling)

125
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:20,940
Hey, it's that
little Tatsudo kid

126
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:24,110
that you taught how to
Buddyfight, big brother.

127
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:26,279
(roars)

128
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,239
Hey, how's it
going, Tatsudo?

129
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:30,325
Well, I'd like to get
into the Buddyfight class.

130
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:34,079
Ever since your lesson, this
little dude's been way obsessed.

131
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,413
Yeah, he's been
begging Ikarino,

132
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:36,665
like, practically every day

133
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:39,584
to transfer into
the Buddyfight program.

134
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:40,627
What can I say?

135
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:44,589
You changed my
life that day, Gao.

136
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:45,674
Glad I could help.

137
00:07:45,674 --> 00:07:46,800
See you later.

138
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:55,016
Wait, before you go!

139
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:57,769
Would you do me the honor
of looking at my deck?

140
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:03,149
I know your schedule
must be very busy,

141
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,777
but I'd appreciate
your advice.

142
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:07,612
Yeah, it'll only
take you a sec.

143
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:08,822
Since you joined
the Buddy Police,

144
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:10,573
we don't see
you much at school.

145
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,242
It'd really
mean a lot to him.

146
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:14,744
♪

147
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,413
Yeah, sure.

148
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:18,206
I'll take a look,
let's see what you got.

149
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:26,715
Crimson Battler Deck.

150
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:27,632
Yes.

151
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:28,883
It's a deck
which allows me

152
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:31,469
to use the Gao Formation
that you taught me.

153
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:34,013
I also have the
same buddy as you.

154
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:37,976
See, Crimson Battler
Drum Bunker Dragon.

155
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:41,187
Huh.

156
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,356
Well, with a
deck like that,

157
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:46,067
you're gonna want to forget
about a Sail Sword, Dragorapter,

158
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,820
and use a Fist Item
like this instead.

159
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:51,489
This here's Crimson
Fist Dragoblaze.

160
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:55,452
It has 3,000 power and only
costs one gauge to equip.

161
00:08:55,452 --> 00:08:57,996
Now, you're probably thinking
it doesn't sound very strong,

162
00:08:57,996 --> 00:09:00,832
but don't be fooled cause
it has a critical of three.

163
00:09:00,832 --> 00:09:03,334
Wow, that's
quite extraordinary.

164
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:04,711
I guess you
could say that.

165
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:07,005
What else, tell me
what other cards to use.

166
00:09:07,005 --> 00:09:10,300
Okay, make sure to put enough
Dragon shields in your deck.

167
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:11,718
Using the
Gao Formation a lot,

168
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:14,345
means leaving your center
position wide open.

169
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:18,016
Always remember, the best
defense is a good offense.

170
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,980
You're a genius.

171
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:25,899
I'm just repeating
what Baku's told me.

172
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,150
Don't be modest.

173
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:28,443
Because of your
help here today,

174
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:31,071
I like Buddyfight even more.

175
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:33,031
Because you like 'em
so much, little brother,

176
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:35,658
you make me like
drawing comics even more.

177
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:37,368
♪

178
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:39,996
What did you‐‐
what did you say?

179
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:44,042
Uh, you make me like
Buddyfight even more?

180
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,585
Think hard, Tatsudo!

181
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:48,588
Tell me why you like to
play Buddyfight so much.

182
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:52,217
Well, I‐‐

183
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:54,385
That's easy.

184
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:57,764
Because it's the most fun
and exciting game there is.

185
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:59,974
♪

186
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,309
Yeah, it is.

187
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:02,560
♪

188
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,770
You're so right!

189
00:10:03,770 --> 00:10:38,972
♪

190
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:52,277
♪

191
00:10:52,277 --> 00:10:53,486
(screams)

192
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:56,948
♪

193
00:10:56,948 --> 00:10:58,491
How long will
he be like this?

194
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:00,451
It's been days now!

195
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:03,788
Before he took off with
Noboru, the 100 Demons guy,

196
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:06,082
Gratos said he'd be
out for quite a while.

197
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:07,792
♪

198
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:08,710
Huh?

199
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,587
Where do you think
you're going?

200
00:11:10,587 --> 00:11:12,463
Not that it's any
of your business,

201
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:14,215
but I'm going to
give him my report.

202
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:19,596
♪

203
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:21,806
‐I'm hungry.
‐Huh?

204
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:26,769
♪

205
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,479
Give me food!

206
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:30,481
I need to eat.

207
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:33,735
(shuddering, screams)

208
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:44,662
(knocking)

209
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,206
Huh?

210
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:51,711
Hey, what are
you doing here?

211
00:11:51,711 --> 00:11:53,296
Is everything okay?

212
00:11:53,296 --> 00:11:55,048
Yeah, I was just
in the neighborhood

213
00:11:55,048 --> 00:11:56,591
and I thought you might
be looking for someone

214
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:59,010
to have a game
of Buddyfight with.

215
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:02,472
Huh?

216
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:03,681
What's that?

217
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:05,058
Your new deck?

218
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:06,100
It's yours.

219
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,769
Your Crimson
Dragon Fist deck.

220
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:10,313
Don't you recognize it?

221
00:12:10,313 --> 00:12:11,522
Come on.

222
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,191
What are you afraid of?

223
00:12:13,191 --> 00:12:15,151
Just a second ago
when I walked in,

224
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:17,779
you were touching your Dragon
World cards, weren't you?

225
00:12:28,206 --> 00:12:32,794
Hmm.

226
00:12:32,794 --> 00:12:35,630
Hey, pal.

227
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:38,383
Why don't you use that
deck and fight with me?

228
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:40,843
Or should I say,
you must fight with me.

229
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:42,595
I don't think I can.

230
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:44,722
You once asked me
to help you train, right?

231
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:48,309
♪

232
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:51,104
What if I challenged you
to a fight to help train me?

233
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:55,108
♪

234
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:56,985
There's always the risk
of something going wrong

235
00:12:56,985 --> 00:12:59,946
when you luminize after a
long time away from the game.

236
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:02,240
So, let's play without
luminizing for now.

237
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,658
Sounds good.

238
00:13:03,658 --> 00:13:06,035
Hey, what's that
deck you're using?

239
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:08,371
It's your Explosive
Dragon Fang deck.

240
00:13:08,371 --> 00:13:10,164
Baku let me borrow it.

241
00:13:10,164 --> 00:13:11,874
So, both of us have
Drum as our buddy?

242
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,251
♪

243
00:13:13,251 --> 00:13:15,586
Yeah, but we'll play
without a buddy this time.

244
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:17,213
Okay, good call.

245
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:18,089
‐Rock.
‐Rock.

246
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,007
‐Paper.
‐Paper.

247
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:21,050
‐Scissors!
‐Scissors!

248
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:22,927
I get the first move.

249
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:23,970
Good luck.

250
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:25,930
‐Time to raise the flag.
‐Time to raise the flag.

251
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,099
‐I fight for Dragon World.
‐I fight for Dragon World.

252
00:13:28,099 --> 00:13:29,600
Charge and draw.

253
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,145
I call Systemic Dagger
Dragon to the center

254
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:33,521
and attack you with it.

255
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:38,026
♪

256
00:13:38,026 --> 00:13:39,819
That's the end of my move.

257
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:42,405
Nice one.

258
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:43,406
Draw.

259
00:13:43,406 --> 00:13:44,657
Charge and draw.

260
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:47,368
I call Crimson Battler Break
Shoulder Dragon to the right

261
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:49,787
and Crimson Battler Spin
Nail Dragon to the left.

262
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:51,581
Look, Gao's playing again.

263
00:13:51,581 --> 00:13:55,293
I pay one gauge and equip
Crimson Fist Dragoblaze.

264
00:13:55,293 --> 00:13:57,045
♪

265
00:13:57,045 --> 00:13:59,130
It's the Gao Formation!

266
00:13:59,130 --> 00:14:04,135
First, I'm gonna attack
Systemic Dagger with Spin Nail.

267
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:06,137
Then, I'll attack you
with Break Shoulder.

268
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:08,431
♪

269
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:11,559
And get ready, cause here
I come again with Dragoblaze.

270
